&lt;p&gt;Join Amylyx at a pivotal moment of growth and visibility as our &lt;strong&gt;Director, Investor Relations&lt;/strong&gt;—a high-impact role at the center of our corporate story, strategy, and market presence. In this position, you’ll work side-by-side with the VP of Investor Relations &amp;amp; Communications and partner closely with our senior leadership team—including our co-CEOs, CFO, CMO, and CCO—to shape how the investment community understands and values our mission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll serve as a strategic advisor and storyteller, helping to translate complex science and financial performance into a clear, compelling narrative that resonates with investors and analysts. You’ll play a key role in strengthening our investor engagement program, building meaningful relationships, and influencing how Amylyx is perceived in a dynamic and evolving healthcare landscape.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the development and execution of investor relations plans and initiatives aligned with corporate goals during a period of dynamic growth, while helping to define and drive a forward-looking 12–24 month IR strategy in partnership with senior leadership and the Board, ensuring alignment with long-term corporate objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage with the investment community, including healthcare investors and equity research analysts, represent Amylyx at events, and, over time, become a primary relationship owner for select sell-side analysts and new buy-side accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write quarterly and annual results communications, including financial results press releases, annual reports, conference call scripts, key messages, Q&amp;amp;As, and other documents to communicate to investor and analyst audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with colleagues to prepare documents for filings and disclosures to be compliant with SEC regulations (i.e., 8-Ks, 10-Ks, 10-Qs, proxies); in certain circumstances, lead creation of documents for filings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write and create investor-facing materials, including press releases, presentations for investor meetings, key message documents, Q&amp;amp;As, and content for website; lead and make update as appropriate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with leadership and other colleagues to ensure consistency of messaging&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in one-on-one meetings, bus tours, conferences, and non-deal roadshows, and lead follow-up when appropriate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond to requests for information from external stakeholders, including shareholders, in a timely manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and analyze analyst research and models, consensus estimates, and market-related trends impacting valuation and perception; summarize market sentiment on Amylyx and continue to manage consensus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze peer companies’ communications, peer sell-side research, industry and communication trends and compile rep

